ates. (1) Create backend/src/main/resources/prompts/hyde.txt — prompt template for generating a short hypothetical answer (2-3 sentences) with plausible planning details for semantic search embedding. Respond with JSON: {\\\"hypotheticalAnswer\\\": \\\"...\\\"}. (2) Create backend/src/main/resources/prompts/sql-synthesis.txt — prompt template for answering analytical questions from pre-computed read model data. Respond with JSON: {\\\"answer\\\": \\\"...\\\", \\\"dataSource\\\": \\\"...\\\", \\\"confidence\\\": 0.85}. (3) Create backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/rag/HydeService.java — @Service with generateHypothetical(question, userId) returning HydeResult record (available, hypotheticalAnswer); uses AiProviderRegistry.generateSuggestion() with TYPE_HYDE; graceful degradation on failure. (4) Create backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/rag/SqlQueryRouter.java — @Service depending on TeamMembershipRepository, UserWeekFactRepository, TeamWeekRollupRepository, RcdoWeekRollupRepository, CarryForwardFactRepository, ComplianceFactRepository, AiProviderRegistry, ObjectMapper. canHandle(intent, keywords) returns true for \\\"analytical\\\" intent, \\\"compliance_query\\\" intent, or \\\"status_query\\\" with aggregation keywords (total, average, most, least, how many, percentage, rate, trend, compare, ranking). query(question, intent, keywords, teamId, timeRangeFrom, timeRangeTo, userId) maps keywords to read model repositories, resolves team member userIds via TeamMembershipRepository.findByTeamId(), queries fact tables with time range (LocalDate.parse with null safety), formats results as JSON context, calls LLM with sql-synthesis prompt, returns SqlQueryResult record (available, answer, dataSource, confidence, suggestionId). (5) Modify backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/provider/AiContext.java — add TYPE_HYDE and TYPE_SQL_SYNTHESIS constants. (6) Modify backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/provider/OpenRouterAiProvider.java — add case entries for